@node inventscorner "Ivent's Corner"
@toc contents
============================================================================
 	    @{b}Ivent's Corner@{ub} - by: @{"Kevin Saunders" link kevinsaunders}
============================================================================

  In recent times I have had more interest in developing for the Amiga 
  Vampire platform.  Over the years I have followed it with great 
  interest.  So far we have 3 games, *Apollo Crown*, *Apollo Blocks* and
  a Tech Demo for *Apollo Menace*. Gunnar and his son Arne are the main 
  coders I work with.   

  We are currently working on *Apollo Space Invaders* and this is a great
  fun game to play and is evolving into something better.

  We have plans on a few new games *Joust* (Arcade conversion), 
  *Arkanoid* clone, *Mutant Monty* remake (Amstrad CPC conversion.  I 
  have made all the maps for both games and focusing now on the redrawing
  of various elements such as the enemies or menu design.

  The big news though is a brand new game, exclusive for V2 and V4 card 
  Vampire machines is a vertical shoot-em-up called *RED DWARF STAR*, 
  some fans may have noticed the posting recently. I decided to simplify 
  the title as some people understandably got confused with another 
  shooter I am proud to be part of with Richard Loewenstein 
  *Reshoot Proxima III* we are getting ever closer to the release of this
  game (later this year). Richard, I'm sure this will be our best version 
  yet, impressive coding, it seems almost magical.  Technically speaking
  I'll be pushing every part of the hardware.  The main difference 
  between the V2 and V4 is the 16bit sound for all V4.
 
  If you would like to see from a day-to-day perspective what I work on 
  please come visit my own Discord channel.  Post feedback on games, 
  suggest games to port, or just hang around in the background.  I would 
  say this is the best way to see up-to-date changes if you're 
  interested.

  https://discord.gg/K3f7UyYDT9

  Discord is my main communication channel between all the developers I 
  work with and it's far quicker to post a quick update.

  *_Other News:_*
  If you have not seen the latest info on the Apollo range of 
  Accelerators, the team have just announced the Manticore V4+ 
  Accelerator for the A600.  For more info please visit here:

  http://www.apollo-core.com/knowledge.php?b=1&note=38662

  *_Other games:_*

  *International Karate Masters*

  Another game that is quietly being worked on for V2, and V4 machines is 
  a game called *International Karate Masters*, I'll be helping with 
  background scenery and possible pixel cleanups of the characters, more 
  info coming soon.  I've been a big fan of IK+ on the Amiga and am 
  excited to be part of this.

  Amiga Forever.
  Invent | Kevin Saunders

@endnode

